      "question": "If the coordinates of the vertices of a parallelogram $ABCD$ are $A(1, 2)$, $B(4, 3)$, $C(6, 6)$, find the coordinates of the fourth vertex $D(x, y)$.",
      "answer": "$(3, 5)$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Use the property that diagonals of a parallelogram bisect each other.",
          "Equate midpoints of $AC$ and $BD$."
